description:
The Birth of Chthon? Last Issue!

Victoria Montesi is impregnated with Chthon while Dr. Strange takes him on in his dimension.
name: Born Again?
Guys Part 7

description:
After escaping the Himalayas, Garth takes Dolphin and Aquaman to Thierna Na Oge.

In the underwater city of Thierna Na Oge, two sisters, Nuada Silverarm and Bres, are engaged in mystic combat. Ultimately, the victor is Silverarm, who exiles her sister, rather than execute Bres. With the conflict ended, Silverarm instructs her people to prepare for the coming of Aquaman. En route from the Himalayas, Tempest and Dolphin ferry the injured Sea King to Thierna Na Oge, aboard Aquaman's telepathically controlled thinkship. Left behind in the Himalayas, the villainous Admiral Strom is picked up by an immense, skull shaped, meteor ship. Meanwhile, in the aftermath of another conflict, Koryak discovers that Atlan is, in fact, not buried in debris, but, according to Kordax, has teleported away. Apparently in response to Bres' call, the meteor ship arrives, at her behest, to end her exile. Aquaman awakens in Thierna Na Oge, being tended to by Silverarm. Aware of Aquaman's goals for the Seven Golden Cities, Silverarm pledges the unconditional support of Thierna Na Oge to the Sea KIng. Tempest and Dolphin discuss Aquaman's "Mission of Unity", which has brought them to Thierna Na Oge. When Dolphin remarks on how much Tempest has changed, the young hero steals a kiss from her, then swims away.

The meteor ship descends down upon Thierna Na Oge. While Silverarm assembles a conclave to repel the skull-shaped scout ship, Aquaman telepathically summons his own vessel, and mounts a delaying action against the invading ship. Aquaman fires on the meteor ship, damaging it enough for it to turn it's focus on him. Before Aquaman's ship can be destroyed, Silverarm's conclave unleash a powerful mystic assault on the meteor ship, blasting it to fragments. Armored invaders pour into the sea, abandoning the meteor ship. Aquaman, Tempest and Dolphin join Silverarm's conclave in repelling the invaders. Aquaman summons sharks to aid in the battle against the invaders. During the conflict, Dolphin is overwhelmed by a sudden compulsion to slay Aquaman. Leveling her weapon upon him, Dolphin takes careful aim, but at the last moment, fires on one of the invaders. Bres makes her presence known, leading the invaders against Thierna Na Oge. No longer willing to abide her sister's actions, Silverarm disintegrates Bres. With Bres' death, the invaders flee. Aquaman suspects their easy victory in the skirmish bodes ill for the true battle to come. The invaders have taken their measure now, and will be better prepared when next they strike. Strom is returned to his base of operations, with dreams of conquest gleaming in his eyes.
name: First Strike!

first_appearance_locations.name: Jean Grey School for Higher Learning

location_credits.name: Jean Grey School for Higher Learning

description: Captain Marvel (aka Monica Rambeau) falls under the control of the Controller! And the diabolical super-villain commands her to capture the son of the first Captain Marvel! To that end the former avenger zooms to Titan and ambushes Starfox and Legacy (aka Genis-vell)! When Monica returns to Earth with Legacy, the battle of (captain) marvels begins! Will the Controller get his long-awaited revenge? Or will the Avengers take control before it's too late?
name: Legacies

description: While Luse is being beaten to a pulp by his kidnapper, Morachi meets with the great wizard Mogre-Ur. What about you ask? You read the pages of text.
name: Sanctuary Book 3: Guild War One: Pain

description: This issue picks up where the previous issue left off, as Catwoman tries to escape the ship only to be shortly after recaptured, and meet the master mind of her abduction The Collector. Who offers her a job in search of the wheel of plagues,if she survives the booby traps surrounding it.
name: The Razor's Edge

description: Commissioner Gordon found Batman at the scene, still unconscious. He continued to fight his dreams as Narcosis and company created their poisons. Batman finally awakened and thanked Jim. Narcosis broke into and took over a dairy plant to poison Gotham City's milk.
name: The Nightmare Man

description: This wiki page is a stub. Hit the edit button above to add to this article.
name: Ludwig's Children
Road Trip! Part 2 - Siege Most Perilous

description: With the help of Jay Garrick, Superman puts a stop to the tornados going through Kansas.
name: Blown Away!

description:
Dirk Morgna returns--but will this "Sun Boy" join the Legion or engulf it in an all-consuming inferno?

Dirk Morgna has been quarantined to a lab ever since he was irradiated and given the ability of super heat luminance. Now Dirk wants out and won't let Science Police or Legionnaire stop him from seeing his father.
name: Sundown

description: Gilbert Hernandez continues here in excellent form as he treats us to the adventures of three wild young ladies, Gabby, Maribel, and Kitten, who are attempting to rescue their friend, Una, from prison in order to celebrate their birthdays -- which all happen to fall on the same day! Sweet sixteen, indeed! It's got wrestling robots, high-speed chases, tax collecting, and super heroics -- isn't that enough for ya?!

The plan was for the new Heartbreakers to help retrieve that pesky genetic virus, the Paracelsus Matrix, from Biovoc's corporate clutches. But then Queenie went and got captured, so now they've gotta rescue her before she becomes the next experimental subject for the Matrix! Will Club Squad's first mission turn out to be their last? Will Queenie live to fight another day? It's all-out action (along with some quiet reflection) in the happenin' Heartbreakers tradition as these questions and more are answered!
Through eldritch forests, uncharted oceans, and the desert lair of some particularly noxious beasts, Cain, Abel, and Gregory search for a sign of Goldie and the amoral charmer who has abducted her.
name: The Goldie Factor, Part Two

description: Flex Mentallo relives his final battle against the Menace of the Mentallium Man and meets the deadly Killer Kitten, who provides an ominous clue toward finding his former comrade The Fact.
name: "After the Fact", Part Two: My Beautiful Head

description:
All hell breaks loose as Hitman realizes too late that his assignment to execute the Joker was a setup: the Mawzir, a gun-wielding demon, is closing in to recruit Tommy Monaghan as an assassin for the Arkanonne, two bullet-ridden demonlords. Meanwhile, Batman is on Hitman's tail as well...and the Dark Knight may be an even bigger problem for Monaghan than going to hell.

Tommy, Batman and a six armed murder-demon are tearing through the basements of Arkham Asylum. Innocent lives are in danger and even the Joker takes a bullet!
name: A Rage in Arkham, Part Three

description: A war is brewing in "Up in the Sky." The Gulag, which is a prison that houses super-powered villains, is on the verge of bursting open at the seams, and the heroes must act.
name: Up In The Sky

description: Terry Gilliam's Brazil meets The Maltese Falcon in Terminal City, a groundbreaking 9-issue Vertigo mini-series set in an immense deco-futurist world, filled with intrigue, action, conspiracies, shady dealings, persistent mysteries...even a reluctant hero or two. Structured as three linked 3-part stories, Terminal City is nothing less than hypnotic, as an extraordinary cast of characters winds its way through an urban labyrinth. Written with insight and humor by Mister X creator Dean Motter, Terminal City is beautifully illustrated by Michael Lark. Painted covers are rendered by Mark Chiarello.
name: Episode One

description: Now that Una is out of prison -- a birthday gift from her pals Gaby, Maribel, and Kitten -- the sparks really fly! Hernandez concludes this wild romp with his usual high-caliber storytelling!

name: Bred Up In Darkness - Part 2: Blood Of The Son

description:
Overview
Spiking trees, hammering equipment, and setting cranes ablaze -- that's what the eco-activists call "Night work," and Concrete's in the thick of it! Emotionally primed for sabotage -- if not actual confrontation -- Concrete and his companions make use of the stone man's incredible night vision and tremendous strength to wreak major damage on some logging equipment. It seems like exciting and righteous work. And then the men with the rifles show up...

Overview

In his quest to find the vampire Vladimir Giurescu, Hellboy must battle the flying metal fist of a bald Nazi supermonster! Danger lurks in every corner of Castle Giurescu, and Hellboy's prepared to meet it head-on! In the back-up, "Silent as the Grave," we meet the second half of the new mystery team, as the MonsterMen confront a monstrous Jib-Bic, in beautifully weird images that only new Legend member Gary Gianni (The Shadow: Hell's Heat Wave) could cook up.
name: Chapter Two

description: For all of the pain, humiliation, and suffering he's put him through, Hartigan's gonna wipe that yellow bastard all over this forty-eight page finale!

person_credits.role: writer, artist, penciler, letterer, inker, cover

description:
Overview

In the past, the Lord of the Apes has risked his life to save many people -- some of whom he called friend and others for whom he had no name. Now, it is Jane who needs saving. She is dying, the result of a mysterious virus. And with no one to battle, no savage creatures to fend off, for the first time in his life, Tarzan feels helpless.

The war between the Neko ninjas and the Komori ninja resumes. Chizu, the leader of the Neko ninjas is transporting a secret document, and when she meets up with Usagi, he is compelled to help her against the Komori.
name: Bats, The Cat, and the Rabbit

person_credits.name: Stan Sakai
person_credits.role: writer, artist, penciler, letterer, inker, cover

description: Only seconds out of the grave and with Diana unconscious, Artemis finds herself ambushed by a strange group of warriors. She rescues a female security officer named Hank Jessup in the process just as more and more of the warriors arrive. She is offered a spot on a covert, demon-hunting team and travels to Pennsylvania to meet their leader Nathaniel and his right hand woman Shock Treatment but all is not as it seems.
name: Tribes

description: A volcano on the island began to erupt - everyone was ordered to leave or get to the coast. Azrael, under hypnotic control, fought his doctor's brother. After defeating him, he began getting people to safety. Orchid, his brother, and Azrael were not among the people who made it off the island before it was destroyed.
name: Angel in Flames part three: Save the Innocents
The Deadman Connection part 3

description:
It's no laughing matter to Harley Quinn when her occasional partner Poison Ivy gets herself a new sidekick--Robin, the Boy Wonder?! Will the joke be on Harley or the teen hero?

In this ish, Robin is being mind controlled by Poison Ivy! He becomes close to her, which Harley doesn`t find all that cool...
name: Harley and Ivy and... Robin?

description:
In a fascist future society, a mother tells her young son the legend of the Batman.

Batman ponders what turns children into murderers.

Batman is too late to save a young boy and his family from being brutally gunned down, before being wounded himself. Left to die, the hero has a conversation with the city that is his home.

Batman looks for the evidence that could lock away a murderer.

Batman and the Joker wait in the green room for Commissioner Gordon's scene to end.

The Dark Knight must make a final stand against a pair of bioengineered soldiers-turned-killing-machines--or die trying. But as the battle rages, Batman discovers each monstrosity carries a weapon that could devastate all of Gotham. "Infected" part 2.
name: Infected Part 2 of 2

volume.name: Batman: Legends of the Dark Knight

description:
Tim wanders around London, still determined to avoid his family and friends so as to keep them from harm--and of course he also thinks they mostly reject him now.

He passes out in an alley from lack of food.

The Wobbly (last seen in issue 14) shows up and intends to collect him, thinking he has thrown away himself, but Kenny (last seen in the first issue) shows up and stops him, saying that Tim is actually on the road.

We next see Kenny visiting the waitress (last seen in Arcana Annual 1) to get some food for Tim. He's been caring for Tim for a while. Kenny watches as Tim sleeps, and his tattoos transform into living animals and attack each other. Kenny wakes Tim up, and the tattoos (which Kenny calls maps) continue to battle.

The scorpion tries to sting the butterfly but hits the lit candle and burns up. The butterfly comes back and Tim slaps it into a new, smaller location on his arm. Kenny admonishes Tim for letting Circe put them on him in the first place, but also says Tim is not ready to let go of the butterfly.

Kenny then tells Tim he can take any one thing from his knapsack, which turns out to have tickets to locations all over the world.

Tim decides to go to San Francisco to see Zatanna. Arriving in the airport, he is already amazed at American customs and sights when he runs into Leah, the succubus he freed (last seen in issue 8). She's now a teen model, touring around with a van full of other teen models.

She gets Tim to jump in, and they all ride off. Leah is not unhappy to hear that Tim isn't seeing Molly any more.
name: Rites of Passage, Prologue: Into Thin Air

description: "Race Against Time - Chapter Three: Speed Metal." Wally's trip through the timestream finds him in the 27th century, home of speedster John Fox. Meanwhile, Linda cozies up to the blue-clad Flash from the future, and Iris West is forced by the new Polaris to write The Life Story of The Flash.
name: Race Against Time Part 3

description:
Grayven has already defeated the Darkstars and Adam Strange. Now the only thing standing between him and total victory is the last Green Lantern.

Adam Strange wakes up as Grayven starts attacking Kyle. Donna retrieves the wounded John Stewart. She gets him back to their hq and they try to give him some medical help. His heart stops. Kyle meanwhile holds of the would be Conqueror Grayven who reveals he is the bastard son of Darkseid and all the destruction, the planets and the darkstars has been to get his fathers attention and then he will usurp his fathers throne by his destruction.

Donna manages to resuscitate john and he orders them to continue their assault and defend the planet. Kyle and grayven continue to tangle and Kyle is apparently knocked out. Donna and Adam arrive on the battle filed and rally the remaining darkstars.

Grayven orders his lieutenant to find the teleporter so they can depart. Kyle arrives takes the

fight straight to Grayven. John pulls himself slowly towards the teleporter since he realizes Kyle can’t beat grayven. Grayven mows down Kyle with his eye beams and john hits the teleporter it misses however BUT it gives Kyle the moment he needs to push him towards the beam and he’s gone. Leaderless his lieutenant retreats. Kyle tends to John and then must try and stop the floating city from falling. Using all the knowledge he gained from Batman, Spectre, Shazam and Wonderwoman he accomplishes his task. On the battlefield the darkstars are finished Meryan and Donna quite to leave with John and Kyle respectively leaving only four darkstars active. Kyle takes everyone back to earth finally coming into his own and acknowledging he’s a hero.
name: Last Stand!

description: In order to understand the nature of his lost dark side, John Constantine pays a surprise visit to the "most evil man in the world," a harvester of worms with a horrible, if peculiar, secret. "Difficult Beginnings" part 2.
name: Difficult Beginnings, Part Two: The Trouble with Worms

description: Impulse must find a stolen ancient artifact and source of power known as the "Eye of God," and the prime suspects are the Trickster and White Lightning.
name: Trust

description: When Lord Fanny and King Mob are trapped by the Invisibles' enemies and infected with reality-altering, cancerous nanomachines, the rest of the Invisibles--led by Jim Crow--must break them out. ''House of Fun'' part 1 of 3.
name: House Of Fun
Purge, Part 2: To Say Goodbye

description:
On the morning after his fateful back-alley rendezvous, a boiling-mad Starr is looking for revenge. Meanwhile, Jesse Custer and his crew crash in on Jesus de Sade and discover a party of positively Babylonian proportions...

Starr's search for Jesse, and Jesse's search for De Sade lead to the biggest, most hedonistic party on the west coast.
name: Crashing The Party (Hunters Part 3)

description: Robin and Wildcat (Ted Grant) teamed up to go after the Speedboyz - a group of car thieves who'd gotten off on a technicality. They got them and gave them over to the police. Batman learned from Gordon that the Clench was back and more powerful.
name: Up to Speed

description: Witness the birth of a classic Starman villain as the Golden Age Sandman and Ted Knight search for answers behind the mysterious mist-related crimes.
name: The Mist: Act Four of Four
The Age Of Innocence (Falling Down To Heaven Part One)

description: The Spectre faces off against the spirit of an abusive husband who was killed by his tormented wife. A fragment from the American Talisman is given to Helen Belcanto, a dissatisfied editor, with interesting results.
name: Shattered Glass

description:
Part 1 of the 4-part ''Sand and Stars'' storyline! On a quest to uncover the Mist's coveted medal, Starman must leave Opal City and find one of his father's former allies--Wesley Dodds, the Golden Age Sandman!

Following his confrontation with Nash, Jack dreams of her and the two of them together. Oddly his dream ends with an image of the Golden-Age Sandman. After talking to his dad, Jack heads to New York City, and a visit with Wesley Dodds and his paramour, author Dian Belmont.
name: Sand and Stars, Part One

description:
When a gigantic volcanic rock rises out of the sea, a team of scientists investigates. When they go missing, Superboy and Knockout follow their trail!

Superboy tries to stop a madman using a volcano to endanger innocent lives. However, his best ally is Knockout, who could be much more of a threat then any volcano and has already taken an innocent life.
name: Losin' It! Part 5 of 6: Imminent Eruption!

description: 'Trial by Fire,' part 3 of 6. Mark Millar's climactic Swamp Thing storyline continues: As Swamp Thing plots to destroy all life on Earth, the Phantom Stranger's agents oppose him on two fronts: The Word cuts a bloody swath through the elemental community, and a strangely changed Anton Arcane confronts Swamp Thing directly - for the final time.
name: Trial by Fire, Part 3: The Last Temptation of Anton

description: Can even Wonder Woman survive an assault by the monster that killed Superman? The Amazing Amazon takes on Doomsday, and the mystery surrounding these recent attacks begins to unfold.
name: Level 3

description: WildStar and his companions wander into the underground homeless freaks, and become their leaders to avoid being killed. While Rapture searches for him, Dragon and his fellow Police officers confront and do battle with WildStar and his new team, during which WildStar has some kind of "out-of-body-experience," where he sees the Dragon in the far future.

Spawn freefalls through the levels of Hell where he he undergoes a physical and psychological baptism. Layers of Al Simmons' life are peeled away and his weaknesses are exposed. Finally, Malebolgia rips Al's heart out. Meanwhile, Terry's doctors are still puzzled by his miraculous recovery while Cyan refuses to give up a filthy shoelace she found at the hospital. Elsewhere, Sam shows Twitch their new '55 Chevy car.
name: Freefall
Truth On Trial

description: The Avengers are stretched thin as their enemies rampage through New York City. But it's up to all-too-human Jarvis to face the final threat alone.
name: History Repeats Itself

description: Captain America has to fight the very people he swore to defend. He will never be the same again.
name: Man Without a Country, Part 4: Executive Action

description: Once again, DD fights Spidey!
name: Charming Devils

description:
X-Cutioner hunts down Skin!

Skin and Chamber defeat the X-Cutioner.
name: The Teeth of Our Skin

description: Sabretooth has spent some time in the X-Mansion being rehabilitated. As in the main universe, he escapes in the chaos. Here, he succeeds, killing many X-Heroes where before none have died.
name: Scream in the Night
One Step Forward

description:
Are the X-Men prepared for the unstoppable return of the Juggernaut?

Today the X-Men being to face the battle of their lives, Juggernaut has come to them for the questions about a foe that could mean the end to all life on earth, Professor Xavier's mysterious behavior has took a turn for the worse something cannonball cannot possibly shake of his shoulders, Betsy's newly aqquired Crimson Dawn Tatto begins to trouble her newly found relationship more and more, but one question still remains.....Who is Onslaught?
name: Dark Horizon

first_appearance_locations.name: Jean Grey School for Higher Learning

location_credits.name: Jean Grey School for Higher Learning

description:
Aquaman travels to the floating city of Basilia to free its guardian from the invaders!

In a dungeon, deep within the floating city of Basilia, a man named Spought is being whipped by a sadistic woman. Aquaman dramatically enters through the wall and disarms the woman. Dodging Aquaman's harpoon shot, the woman fires her blaster at Aquaman, but her blast is blocked by a mystic shield protecting the Sea King. With her focus on Aquaman, the woman is open to an attack from Spought, who, despite being chained to the wall, manages to kick her into unconsciousness. Aquaman releases Spought, then continues on with his mission. In another part of Basilia, Tempest and Dolphin, having separated from Aquaman to better explore the city, witness the arrival of an alien ship. One that quickly releases ground forces to storm Basilia. Spought has been the advance man for the invading forces for centuries, serving as a kind of "watchdog" over the machines that power Basilia. In that time, Spought developed a deep and abiding love for the human race, and now seeks to protect it from his people. To that end, Spought has locked down the operating systems on Basilia, keeping the alien forces from fully taking command of the city. Aquaman and Spought stealthily move about Basilia, ducking patrols. Unfortunately, their luck doesn't hold, and soon enough they find themselves taking fire from the alien soldiers. Unexpectedly, Aquaman's mystic shield not only deflects the blasts, but redirects them back on the soldiers, taking out the entire patrol.

In truth, it was not Aquaman's protective shield that won the day, but the arrival of Aquaman's father, the sorcerer, Atlan. Maintaining cover, Tempest suddenly senses the presence of Atlan on the island. Aquaman, Atlan, and Spought don the downed soldiers' armor. Atlan has just come from a hidden city beneath Tritonis, where the Atlanteans have settled. To Aquaman's dismay, his people have fallen under the sway of Kordax the Accursed, and are even now assaulting the city of Tritonis. With the patrols focusing their hunt on Tempest and Dolphin, Aquaman, Atlan, and Spought are able to move more freely through Basilia. However, Spought's torturer has anticipated their arrival in Basilia's control room, and sets up an ambush. While Aquaman and Atlan savagely battle against the alien forces arrayed against them, Spought reaches the floating city's controls. Sealing the command center, Spought pilots the floating city high into the atmosphere, then rolls Basilia. The invading forces tumble into the sea. Tempest and Dolphin are also pitched into the ocean, but Tempest uses his mystical abilities to form a water spout that carries them back to the city. Aquaman instructs Spought to pilot Basilia to Tritonis. The long journey gives Aquaman and Atlan the time for a heart-to-heart conversation. At that moment, in Washington, D.C. the alien envoy, Shaxak, is meeting with the President of the United States.
name: Reunions

description: ONSLAUGHT RISES! The greatest threat mutantkind has ever known is more powerful than ever, and only Cable stands between him and total domination!
name: Never Is A Very Short Time

first_appearance_locations.name: Jean Grey School for Higher Learning

location_credits.name: Jean Grey School for Higher Learning

description:
Overview

From that first issue of Dark Horse Presents to the most recent issue of Sin City, Dark Horse has been bringing you the finest in comics entertainment for ten years. To commemorate our 10th anniversary, we're serving up a special treat: an all-new, four-issue miniseries by the best of the best! From the most celebrated creator-owned work to the most popular of our licensed features, each issue is packed with the same kind of excitement that has been the hallmark of Dark Horse since 1986!

Includes:

  • Daddy’s Little Girl
  • A Brief History Of Dark Horse Comics
  • Predator: 1718
  • Dark Horse Trading Cards
  • The Devil’s Week
  • Hindsight

After being beaten Luse goes back to 
Parintachinland. Parintachin tries to force Luse back out to fight his attackers but Luse has all but given up until Par mentions something from Luse's past.
name: Two: Anger

description: Continuing the adventures of Catwoman and Umberto as they avoid the deadly ancient traps in search of the wheel of plagues. Eventually finding it the three are captured by Bane for Ras Al Ghul.
name: The Wheel of Plagues

description: Henry Bendix decides to reorganize Stormwatch to face the sophisticated and complex threats they face on Earth. He gathers some new members to join his team and dismisses several more from active duty. Henry Bendix decides to have three squads: Stormforce Prime, Stormforce Black and Stormforce Red. Their first mission is to stop a super-powered, murdering psychopath named Father.

Batman made it back to the cave still feeling the after-effects of Narcosis' gas attack. Robin searched, but could come up with no leads on the man. Gordon stationed men at possible targets in attempt to catch him. Batman realized they would have to poison something with a short shelf-life. He took them down at the dairy plant.
name: Safe as Milk
Road Trip! Part 3 - Knights of Gotham

description: Brainiac, in Superman's body, puts a force field over Metropolis; Superman, in Chas's body, escapes the psychiatric hospital and breaks into Metropolis.
name: Identity Crisis III: Snares

description:
The Legion's mission to Starboy's home planet turns downright weird when the team is attacked by a group of rogue heroes. Plus, Ultra Boy discovers the shocking cause of his recent bouts of pain.

Star Boy returns to his homeworld with several Legionnaires to plead his case to remain with the Legion. There, the team must fight the local heroes, the Uncanny Amazers, to secure Star Boy's Legion membership. Back at headquarters, Ultra Boy isn't feeling so well and it's beginning to seem like he's being haunted. But by whom?
name: Lifestyles of the Dead

description: Their predecessors were the World's Finest team. Can the new Green Lantern and Green Arrow team live up to the legacy set before them? Story continues in Green Arrow (1987-1998 1st Series) #110.
name: Hard-Traveling Heroes: the Next Generation part 1: Family Traditions

story_arc_credits.name: Hard Traveling Heroes: The Next Generation

first_appearance_storyarcs.name: Hard Traveling Heroes: The Next Generation

description: Cain and Abel have finally found Goldie and her seductively deceitful companion. But it may already be too late to keep the infant gargoyle from her true destiny--one that will alter the fate of every living creature on Earth.
name: The Goldie Factor, Part Three

description:
Flex Mentallo's quest enters a dark, violent, sexually twisted phase, echoed in the recollections of a mysterious, suicidal young man. Is it the end of everything, or simply the onset of a depraved spandex bacchanal?

It's the ultimate super-hero apocalypse as Flex Mentallo's quest enters a dark and twisted phase, echoed in the recollections of a mysterious, suicidal young man. Is it the end of everything, or just a depraved Spandex orgy?
name: "After the Fact", Part Three: Dig The Vacuum

description:
It's never a good idea to get on a mob boss's bad side, particularly when the mob boss is Moe Dubelez, and the bad side is his deceased ""Siamese"" twin, Joe. Joe was offed a while back by Hitman, and has spent the time since busily decomposing and raising a stench only heaven could cure. Seeking vengeance, brother Moe hires his own hitman to kill Tommy Monaghan--a cold-blooded pro named Johnny Navarone.

It's flashback time as someone close to Tommy is destined to die. And his dear friend Natt the Hat has just shown up. So has a bunch of ninja killers.
name: Ten Thousand Bullets, Part 1

description: In "Never-Ending Battle," a possessed (by Lex Luthor) Captain Marvel battles Superman, and the world is at war. Wonder Woman and the other classic heroes must reclaim the world from the new, ruthlessly violent generation of anti-heroes. Thus concludes Kingdom Come, arguably the greatest Elseworlds tale ever told.
name: Never-Ending Battle

description:
The story begins with an old man and a young guy sitting out on a park bench eating pizza. The young man's a mercenary of some sort and the old man asks him if he's heard the story of the greatest killer of them all...they called him the Saint of Killers.

Thus begins the story of the man who'd become the Saint heading down home to get back to his house where his family and sick children live.
name: Saint of Killers Part 1

description: Theories about the contents of the amnesiac's mysterious briefcase abound--including Professor N. Marion's hypothesis, which states that the case is not of this Earth. Meanwhile, Captain Habib keeps a close eye on Lil and her thugs, whose corrupt plans reek of political overtones. And a smoke bomb hurled by a gas-masked assailant brings the mysterious Lady in Red to the rescue. Plus, a homeless and jobless young B.B. looks for work at the Herculean Arms Hotel.
name: Episode Two

description: The Gen-13 team recuperate as Fairchild tries to reconcile her since now distant and detached father abroad. The Gen-13 try to locate a new deputy leader to their goals petitioning Burnout for the lead, but Burnout rejects the idea out of spite for Lynch. A fight falls once more between Gen-13 and the Deviants which falls flat and the team repairs itself. Plus, a section of fan poetry from the fan letters section.

After the battle with the Lizard People in the Lost Land, Andy runs off on his own and Turok follows to find out what is going on.

Note: Issue also has "Resurrection Rise 2," a four-page preview to the video game.

Final issue.
name: Runaway

description:
Overview
The conclusion to Think Like a Mountain proves the pen is mightier than 1,200 pounds of living stone! Concrete and his Earth First! friends have failed to prevent their forest from becoming yet another clear cut -- when the national press comes to their rescue. Concrete's tracks through the old-growth forest have been mistaken for those of Bigfoot, creating a media circus as reporters and big-game hunters alike converge to hunt for the legendary creature!

The Devil awakens! Hellboy finds the coffin of Vladimir Giurescu just in time to see the two-hundred-year-old vampire rise from a fifty-year sleep. Outside Castle Giurescu, Rasputin initiates a new servant from the ranks of his old Nazi cohorts, and an unlucky group of Bureau agents wakes up something completely unexpected. In the back-up, Gary Gianni's MonsterMen take on a bloated gargoyle and outwit the cops, but not the press.
name: Chapter Three

first_appearance_teams.name: Bureau for Paranormal Research and Defense

team_credits.name: Bureau for Paranormal Research and Defense

description: Jane will die of a bizarre virus if Tarzan cannot find the white dahlia, a rare flower thought to counteract the disease. Between the Lord of the Apes and this herbal cure stand enormous, mutated spiders and deadly, six-legged lions! And as brutal as both may be, they will fall before the might of "Tarzan's Jungle Fury"!
